<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🤖 AI001 Week 8 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Final Project — Your Own App · <strong>Course:</strong> AI Coding with Replit Agent · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes (plus build time)</p>
<p>This is the big one. You will combine <strong>every</strong> skill from the past 7 weeks — specific prompts, context and examples, step-by-step building, iteration, debugging, and understanding code — to build your <strong>own</strong> app from start to finish. The idea must be yours.</p>
<p><strong>Your project must include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>an idea that comes from <strong>you</strong>,</li>
<li>at least <strong>5 prompt steps</strong> to build it,</li>
<li>at least <strong>3 iteration prompts</strong> to improve it,</li>
<li>at least <strong>1 debugging</strong> moment,</li>
<li>a <strong>note</strong> explaining what the key parts of your code do.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Plan Your Idea 🔮</h2>
<p>Before you touch the keyboard, plan. Saying the plan out loud first makes the building much smoother.</p>
<p><strong>Write your idea in one sentence.</strong> "I want to build …"</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Now split that idea into 5 to 7 steps</strong> (remember Week 4 — first, then, finally). Write the step prompts in order.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Step 1:</p>
<p>Step 2:</p>
<p>Step 3:</p>
<p>Step 4:</p>
<p>Step 5:</p>
<p>Step 6 (if needed):</p>
<p>Step 7 (if needed):</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Build, Iterate, Debug 🐛</h2>
<p>Run your steps in Replit one at a time. As you go, you will need to <strong>iterate</strong> (change just one part) and <strong>debug</strong> (explain an error). Keep a record here.</p>
<p><strong>Iteration prompts you used</strong> (at least 3) — write each one and what it changed:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Change 1: … → it changed …</p>
<p>Change 2: … → it changed …</p>
<p>Change 3: … → it changed …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>A bug you hit and fixed</strong> — what was broken, what the error said, and how the AI fixed it:</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Finished App 📸</h2>
<p>When your app works, send the <strong>public link</strong> to it, <strong>or</strong> a <strong>video</strong> of it running. Then explain your project using these sentence starters — write 5 to 7 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I built an app that …</p>
<p>I chose this idea because …</p>
<p>I split my idea into … steps.</p>
<p>The hardest problem was … and I solved it by …</p>
<p>The trickiest part of the code is …</p>
<p>One thing I am proud of is …</p>
<p>If I built it without AI, I would have to start by …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Final Presentation 🎥</h2>
<p>Record a short video (your phone, or a parent's phone) presenting your app, as if showing it to the class. Try to use these words: <strong>prompt</strong>, <strong>step</strong>, <strong>iterate</strong>, <strong>debug</strong>, <strong>understand</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your finished app running.</li>
<li>Read your one-sentence idea and show how you split it into steps.</li>
<li>Show one part of the code and explain what it does in your own words.</li>
<li>Tell the biggest problem you hit and how you solved it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Plan it here before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your app link (or a video) + your full prompt list (at least 7–10 prompts) + your code notes to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
